    <note>Wu(3) Jian [20591] Recommended for the exams (xiangju) in 1153, he was recommended three more times and repeatedly failed to earn the jinshi and finally retired to be a gentry-scholar. According to Hymes, p. 307 n. 20, the family lived at the East Gate of Linchuan city, but bought lands in Jinqi county. Their ancestor moved from Jinling (Jiangning), when Southern Tang submitted to Song. Other sources identify them as Jinqi residents and, my guess is, they were probably related to the Jinqi Wu(3). For now, I follow Hymes in identifying them as Linchuan Wu(3). Lu Jiuyuan, WJ, 27.4b-5b. CBD, 2, 1117-8.</note>
